n]\\n]\\n```\\n\\nLet me trace through: k=1, seq is empty, seq[[1]] doesn't \
exist yet. This approach needs care.\\n\\nLet me think again. s[1]=1 means \
value 1 appears once. s[2]=2 means value 2 appears twice. s[3]=2 means value \
3 appears twice. s[4]=3 means value 4 appears three times. So for value v, it \
appears s[v] times. We generate value by \
value.\\n\\n```wolfram\\nSilverman[n_Integer?Positive] := Module[{seq = {}, v \
= 1},\\n  While[Length[seq] < n,\\n    If[v <= Length[seq],\\n      seq = \
Join[seq, ConstantArray[v, seq[[v]]]],\\n      seq = Join[seq, \
