append s[v] copies of v. But s[v] is the v-th element of the sequence, which \
must already have been determined by the time we need it (since the sequence \
grows faster than linearly).\\n\\nFor v=1: append 1 copy of 1. seq = \
{1}.\\nFor v=2: need seq[[2]], but length is 1. However s[2] must be 2 (the \
