\\n  (* For a convex polygon rolling on a surface:\\n     - It rolls on edge \
0, rotating by angle = edge_angle (but we need the \\n       angle subtended \
at the contact point... no, the rotation when rolling \\n       on an edge is \
actually the exterior angle at the next vertex) *)\\n  \\n  (* The total \
rotation per full cycle = 2*Pi for convex polygon *)\\n  (* Sequence: roll on \
edge i (no rotation change, just translation), \\n     then pivot on vertex \
i+1 through exterior angle *)\\n  \\n  (* Actually: when polygon sits on edge \
