i>-2</sub> thereafter, with the first few terms 1, 2, 5, 12, 29, 70, 169, \
408, 985. The half-companion Pell numbers start 1, 3 and then \
<i>P</i><sub><i>n</i></sub>=2<i>P</i><sub><i>n</i>-1</sub>+<i>P</i><sub><i>n</\
i>-2</sub> thereafter, with the first few terms 1, 3, 7, 17, 41, 99, 239, \
